.PP
Decrypts an \f(CW\*(C`ncryptsec\*(C'\fR string with a password. Returns the private key
as a 64\-char lowercase hex string. Validates the bech32 encoding,
\&\f(CW\*(C`ncryptsec\*(C'\fR prefix, version byte (must be \f(CW0x02\fR), and payload size
(must be 91 bytes). Croaks on wrong password, corrupted data, or
invalid format.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`log_n\*(C'\fR parameter is optional. If omitted, the value embedded in
the \f(CW\*(C`ncryptsec\*(C'\fR payload is used. Providing \f(CW\*(C`log_n\*(C'\fR explicitly overrides
the embedded value, which is useful when you know the cost parameter
in advance.
.PP
